# FastAPI backend for Vitalscope AI
from fastapi import FastAPI, Request, BackgroundTasks
from fastapi.responses import JSONResponse
from hashlib import md5
from urllib.parse import urlencode
import aiohttp
import hmac
import hashlib
import os

app = FastAPI()

MERCHANT_ID = "23125555"
MERCHANT_KEY = "sandbox" # Use your real key in production

@app.post("/api/payfast/ipn")
async def payfast_ipn(request: Request, background_tasks: BackgroundTasks):
data = await request.form()
post_data = dict(data)

# Step 1: Validate IP address (skip in sandbox)
# Optional for live environment

# Step 2: Confirm payment with PayFast
async with aiohttp.ClientSession() as session:
headers = {"Content-Type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"}
async with session.post("https://sandbox.payfast.co.za/eng/query/validate", data=post_data, headers=headers) as resp:
response_text = await resp.text()
if "VALID" not in response_text:
return JSONResponse(status_code=400, content={"error": "Invalid payment"})

# Step 3: Verify signature
signature = post_data.pop("signature", None)
sorted_items = sorted(post_data.items())
signature_str = urlencode(sorted_items).replace("%20", "+")
generated_signature = md5((signature_str + "&passphrase=" + MERCHANT_KEY).encode()).hexdigest()

Here’s the backend JWT starter:

python
from fastapi.security import OAuth2PasswordBearer, OAuth2PasswordRequestForm
from jose import JWTError, jwt
from datetime import datetime, timedelta
from fastapi import Depends

SECRET_KEY = \"your-very-secret-key\"  # Change to strong secret!
ALGORITHM = \"HS256\"
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES = 60

oauth2_scheme = OAuth2PasswordBearer(tokenUrl=\"/api/token\")

def create_access_token(data: dict, expires_delta: timedelta | None = None):
    to_encode = data.copy()
    expire = datetime.utcnow() + (expires_delta or timedelta(minutes=ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES))
    to_encode.update({\"exp\": expire})
    return jwt.encode(to_encode, SECRET_KEY, algorithm=ALGORITHM)

async def get_current_user(token: str = Depends(oauth2_scheme), db: Session = Depends(get_db)):
    credentials_exception = HTTPException(status_code=401, detail=\"Could not validate credentials\")
    try:
        payload = jwt.decode(token, SECRET_KEY, algorithms=[ALGORITHM])
        email = payload.get(\"sub\")
        if email is None:
            raise credentials_exception
    except JWTError:
        raise credentials_exception
    user = db.query(User).filter(User.email == email).first()
    if user is None:
        raise credentials_exception
    return user

@app.post(\"/api/token\")
async def login_for_access_token(form_data: OAuth2PasswordRequestForm = Depends(), db: Session = Depends(get_db)):
    user = db.query(User).filter(User.email == form_data.username).first()
    if not user or not pwd_context.verify(form_data.password, user.hashed_password):
        raise HTTPException(status_code=401, detail=\"Incorrect username or password\")
    access_token = create_access_token(data={\"sub\": user.email})
    return {\"access_token\": access_token, \"token_type\": \"bearer\"}

Here’s the updated PatientForm with auth check and token sent in the Authorization header:

jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";
import { useAuth } from "./AuthContext";
import axios from "axios";

export default function PatientForm() {
  const { user, token } = useAuth();
  const [form, setForm] = useState({
    email: "",
    age: "",
    blood_pressure: "",
    temperature: "",
    heart_rate: "",
    symptoms: "",
  });
  const [result, setResult] = useState(null);
  const [error, setError] = useState(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    if (user?.email) {
      setForm((f) => ({ ...f, email: user.email }));
    }
  }, [user]);

  if (!user || !token) {
    return (
      <div className="max-w-xl mx-auto p-6">
        <h2 className="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Please log in to access this page.</h2>
      </div>
    );
  }

  const handleChange = (e) => {
    setForm({ ...form, [e.target.name]: e.target.value });
  };

  const handleSubmit = async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    setError(null);
    setResult(null);

    try {
      const res = await axios.post(
        "/api/analyze-exam",
        {
          ...form,
          age: parseInt(form.age),
          temperature: parseFloat(form.temperature),
          heart_rate: parseInt(form.heart_rate),
        },
        { headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` } }
      );
      setResult(res.data);
    } catch (err) {
      setError(err.response?.data?.detail || "Something went wrong.");
    }
  };

  return (
    <div className="max-w-xl mx-auto p-6">
      <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="grid gap-4">
        <input
          placeholder="Email"
          name="email"
          value={form.email}
          onChange={handleChange}
          required
          readOnly
          className="p-2 border"
        />
        <input
          placeholder="Age"
          name="age"
          value={form.age}
          onChange={handleChange}
          required
          type="number"
          className="p-2 border"
        />
        <input
          placeholder="Blood Pressure (e.g. 120/80)"
          name="blood_pressure"
          value={form.blood_pressure}
          onChange={handleChange}
          required
          className="p-2 border"
        />
        <input
          placeholder="Temperature (°C)"
          name="temperature"
          value={form.temperature}
          onChange={handleChange}
          required
          type="number"
          className="p-2 border"
        />
        <input
          placeholder="Heart Rate (BPM)"
          name="heart_rate"
          value={form.heart_rate}
          onChange={handleChange}
          required
          type="number"
          className="p-2 border"
        />
        <textarea
          placeholder="Symptoms (comma separated)"
          name="symptoms"
          value={form.symptoms}
          onChange={handleChange}
          required
          className="p-2 border"
        />
        <button type="submit" className="p-2 bg-blue-600 text-white">
          Analyze
        </button>
      </form>

      {result && (
        <div className="mt-6 p-4 bg-green-100 rounded">
          <h3 className="font-semibold">Diagnosis: {result.diagnosis}</h3>
          <p className="mt-1">Recommendation: {result.recommendation}</p>
        </div>
      )}

      {error && (
        <div className="mt-6 p-4 bg-red-100 text-red-800 rounded">{error}</div>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

// App.js
import React, { useState, useEffect, createContext, useContext } from "react";
import { View, Text, Button, TextInput, ActivityIndicator, Alert } from "react-native";
import AsyncStorage from "@react-native-async-storage/async-storage";
import * as Linking from "expo-linking";

// --- Auth Context ---
const AuthContext = createContext();

export const useAuth = () => useContext(AuthContext);

export default function App() {
  const [token, setToken] = useState(null);
  const [email, setEmail] = useState("");
  const [password, setPassword] = useState("");
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [userIsPro, setUserIsPro] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    // Load token on app start
    AsyncStorage.getItem("token").then(setToken);
  }, []);

  const login = async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    try {
      const res = await fetch("https://your-backend-url/api/login", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify({ email, password }),
      });
      if (!res.ok) throw new Error("Login failed");
      const data = await res.json();
      setToken(data.token); // You’ll need to update backend to return token
      await AsyncStorage.setItem("token", data.token);
      setUserIsPro(data.is_pro);
    } catch (e) {
      Alert.alert("Error", e.message);
    }
    setLoading(false);
  };

  if (!token) {
    return (
      <View style={{ padding: 20 }}>
        <Text>Email:</Text>
        <TextInput value={email} onChangeText={setEmail} autoCapitalize="none" />
        <Text>Password:</Text>
        <TextInput value={password} onChangeText={setPassword} secureTextEntry />
        <Button title={loading ? "Logging in..." : "Login"} onPress={login} />
      </View>
    );
  }

  return (
    <AuthContext.Provider value={{ token, userIsPro }}>
      <MainApp />
    </AuthContext.Provider>
  );
}

function MainApp() {
  const { token, userIsPro } = useAuth();

  return (
    <View style={{ padding: 20 }}>

            Linking.openURL(payfastUrl);

    return user

import React, { useState } from "react";
import { View, Text, TextInput, Button, Alert, ActivityIndicator, ScrollView } from "react-native";
import AsyncStorage from "@react-native-async-storage/async-storage";

export default function ExamForm() {
  const [age, setAge] = useState("");
  const [bloodPressure, setBloodPressure] = useState("");
  const [temperature, setTemperature] = useState("");
  const [heartRate, setHeartRate] = useState("");
  const [symptoms, setSymptoms] = useState("");
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [result, setResult] = useState(null);

  const submitExam = async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    setResult(null);
    try {
      const token = await AsyncStorage.getItem("token");
      if (!token) throw new Error("Not authenticated");

      const email = await AsyncStorage.getItem("userEmail"); // You can save email at login
      if (!email) throw new Error("Email not found");

      const res = await fetch("https://vitalscope.up.railway.app/api/analyze-exam", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: {
          "Content-Type": "application/json",
          Authorization: `Bearer ${token}`,
        },
        body: JSON.stringify({
          email,
          age: parseInt(age),
          blood_pressure: bloodPressure,
          temperature: parseFloat(temperature),
          heart_rate: parseInt(heartRate),
          symptoms,
        }),
      });

      if (!res.ok) {
        const err = await res.json();
        throw new Error(err.detail || "Failed to analyze exam");
      }

      const data = await res.json();
      setResult(data);
    } catch (e) {
      Alert.alert("Error", e.message);
    }
    setLoading(false);
  };

  return (
    <ScrollView contentContainerStyle={{ padding: 20 }}>
      <Text>Age:</Text>
      <TextInput keyboardType="numeric" value={age} onChangeText={setAge} style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 10 }} />

      <Text>Blood Pressure (e.g. 120/80):</Text>
      <TextInput value={bloodPressure} onChangeText={setBloodPressure} style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 10 }} />

      <Text>Temperature (°C):</Text>
      <TextInput keyboardType="decimal-pad" value={temperature} onChangeText={setTemperature} style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 10 }} />

      <Text>Heart Rate (bpm):</Text>
      <TextInput keyboardType="numeric" value={heartRate} onChangeText={setHeartRate} style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 10 }} />

      <Text>Symptoms:</Text>
      <TextInput
        multiline
        numberOfLines={4}
        value={symptoms}
        onChangeText={setSymptoms}
        style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 20, height: 80, textAlignVertical: "top" }}
      />

      {loading ? (
        <ActivityIndicator size="large" />
      ) : (
        <Button title="Analyze Exam" onPress={submitExam} />
      )}

      {result && (
        <View style={{ marginTop: 20 }}>
          <Text style={{ fontWeight: "bold", fontSize: 18 }}>Diagnosis:</Text>
          <Text>{result.diagnosis}</Text>

          <Text style={{ fontWeight: "bold", fontSize: 18, marginTop: 10 }}>Recommendation:</Text>
          <Text>{result.recommendation}</Text>
        </View>
      )}
    </ScrollView>
  );

          body: JSON.stringify({
            email,
            age: parseInt(age),
            blood_pressure: bloodPressure,
            temperature: parseFloat(temperature),
            heart_rate: parseInt(heartRate),
            symptoms,
          }),
        }
      );

      if (!res.ok) {
        const err = await res.json();
        throw new Error(err.detail || "Failed to analyze exam");
      }

      const data = await res.json();
      setResult(data);
    } catch (e) {
      Alert.alert("Error", e.message);
    }
    setLoading(false);
  };

  return (
    <ScrollView contentContainerStyle={{ padding: 20 }}>
      <Text>Age:</Text>
      <TextInput
        keyboardType="numeric"
        value={age}
        onChangeText={setAge}
        style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 10 }}
      />

      <Text>Blood Pressure (e.g. 120/80):</Text>
      <TextInput
        value={bloodPressure}
        onChangeText={setBloodPressure}
        style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 10 }}
      />

      <Text>Temperature (°C):</Text>
      <TextInput
        keyboardType="decimal-pad"
        value={temperature}
        onChangeText={setTemperature}
        style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 10 }}
      />

      <Text>Heart Rate (bpm):</Text>
      <TextInput
        keyboardType="numeric"
        value={heartRate}
        onChangeText={setHeartRate}
        style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 10 }}
      />

      <Text>Symptoms:</Text>
      <TextInput
        multiline
        numberOfLines={4}
        value={symptoms}
        onChangeText={setSymptoms}
        style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 20, height: 80, textAlignVertical: "top" }}
      />

      {loading ? (
        <ActivityIndicator size="large" />
      ) : (
        <Button title="Analyze Exam" onPress={submitExam} />
      )}

      {result && (
        <View style={{ marginTop: 20 }}>
          <Text style={{ fontWeight: "bold", fontSize: 18 }}>Diagnosis:</Text>
          <Text>{result.diagnosis}</Text>

          <Text style={{ fontWeight: "bold", fontSize: 18, marginTop: 10 }}>
            Recommendation:
          </Text>
          <Text>{result.recommendation}</Text>
        </View>
      )}
    </ScrollView>
  );
}

// --- Main App ---
export default function App() {
  const [token, setToken] = useState(null);
  const [email, setEmail] = useState("");
  const [password, setPassword] = useState("");
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
  const [userIsPro, setUserIsPro] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    // Load token and email on app start
    AsyncStorage.getItem("token").then(setToken);
    AsyncStorage.getItem("userEmail").then(setEmail);
    AsyncStorage.getItem("userIsPro").then((val) => setUserIsPro(val === "true"));
  }, []);

  const login = async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    try {
      const res = await fetch("https://vitalscope.up.railway.app/api/login", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify({ email, password }),
      });
      if (!res.ok) throw new Error("Login failed");
      const data = await res.json();

      setToken(data.access_token);
      setUserIsPro(data.is_pro);

      await AsyncStorage.setItem("token", data.access_token);
      await AsyncStorage.setItem("userEmail", data.email);
      await AsyncStorage.setItem("userIsPro", data.is_pro ? "true" : "false");
    } catch (e) {
      Alert.alert("Error", e.message);
    }
    setLoading(false);
  };

  const logout = async () => {
    setToken(null);
    setEmail("");
    setPassword("");
    setUserIsPro(false);
    await AsyncStorage.clear();
  };

  if (!token) {
    return (
      <View style={{ padding: 20 }}>
        <Text>Email:</Text>
        <TextInput
          value={email}
          onChangeText={setEmail}
          autoCapitalize="none"
          style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 10 }}
        />
        <Text>Password:</Text>
        <TextInput
          value={password}
          onChangeText={setPassword}
          secureTextEntry
          style={{ borderWidth: 1, marginBottom: 10 }}
        />
        <Button title={loading ? "Logging in..." : "Login"} onPress={login} />
      </View>
    );
  }

  return (
    <AuthContext.Provider value={{ token, userIsPro }}>
      <View style={{ padding: 20 }}>
        <Text>Welcome, {email}!</Text>

        {userIsPro ? (
          <ExamForm />
        ) : (
          <Button
            title="Upgrade to Pro"
            onPress={() => {
              const payfastUrl =
                "https://sandbox.payfast.co.za/eng/process?merchant_id=23125555&merchant_key=sandbox&amount=99.99&item_name=Vitalscope+Pro+Subscription&return_url=vitalscope://upgrade-success&cancel_url=vitalscope://upgrade-cancel&notify_url=https://vitalscope.up.railway.app/api/payfast/ipn&email_address=" +
                encodeURIComponent(email);
              Linking.openURL(payfastUrl);
            }}
          />
        )}

        <Button title="Logout" onPress={logout} color="red" />
      </View>
    </AuthContext.Provider>
  );
}
